<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN311-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai - atu; tuṟai - pāṇpāṭṭu. oḷavaiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN311">
      <lg type="edition" style="pūṭṭuvil">
<l>kaḷarppaṭu kūvaṟ ṟōṇṭi nāḷum</l>
<l>pulaitti kaḻīiya tūveḷ ḷaṟuvai</l>
<l>tāteru maṟukiṉ mācuṇa viruntu</l>
<l>palarkuṟai ceyta malartā raṇṇaṟ</l>
<l>koruvaru millai mātō ceruvattuc</l>
<l>ciṟappuṭaic ceṅkaṇ pukaiyavōr</l>
<l>tōlkoṇṭu maṟaikkuñ cālpuṭai yōṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Being in the street with dust [and] dung so that</l>
<l>the pure white cloth washed by the washer woman</l>
<l>daily after hollowed out a pool suffused with saline soil</l>
<l>	absorbs stains,</l>
<l>[now] is there nobody for the majesty with a garland of blossoms</l>
<l>who acted according to the requests of many,</l>
<l>he who is worthy of being covered with [his] one shield,</l>
<l>as [his] red eyes fumed with exultation in a fight?</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
